## Session Structure Pattern
Each session typically contains:
- **Demo/** - Working code examples and demonstrations
- **Docs/** - Documentation, PDFs, and learning materials
- **Task.md** - Assignment instructions (when applicable)

## Teaching Methodology
- **Demo: I code** (20-30 min) - Instructor demonstrates concepts
- **Apply: You code** (15-20 min) - Students practice immediately  
- **Feedback and help** - Interactive assistance
- **Wrap-up** - Summary and homework assignment

## File Naming Conventions
- Session materials use "Session X" format
- Documentation files use descriptive names with .md and .pdf versions
- Demo files are typically index.html, script.js, and style.css
- Settings files use settings-template.json format
